                            <comment id="13054908" author="pete" created="Sat, 25 Jun 2011 14:36:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;additionally, when the first call of tester.startPage() redirects to a secure version of the page, e.g. &lt;a href=&quot;https://localhost/secure&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://localhost/secure&lt;/a&gt;, the subsequent requests (e.g. form submit) should go to the same base url (&lt;a href=&quot;https://localhost&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://localhost&lt;/a&gt;). in general wicket tester should assign the protocol://host:port of the last request to the next wicket tester request (unless the last request was of type ajax).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13054910" author="pete" created="Sat, 25 Jun 2011 14:40:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed in trunk and added a few tests&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
